org.loklak.objects

Class Timeline

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.loklak.objects.Timeline
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<MessageEntry>

    public class Timeline
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<MessageEntry>
    A timeline is a structure which holds tweet for the purpose of presentation There is no tweet retrieval method here, just an iterator which returns the tweets in reverse appearing order

      • getPrecursorTweet

        private MessageEntry getPrecursorTweet()
        get the precursor tweet, which is the latest tweet that the user has seen. It is the tweet which appears at the end of the list. This tweet may be used to compute the insert date which is valid for new tweets. Therefore there is a cache which contains the latest tweet shown to the user so fa. New tweets must have an entry date after that last tweet to create a stable list
        Returns:
        the last tweet that a user has seen. It is also the oldest tweet that the user has seen.
